com.camerontec.catalys.server.routing

Interface ILink

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Cloneable, EventListener, ICatalysEventListener, IComponent, IConfigurable, IEndOfDayPerformer, IExceptionListener, IFIXListener, IFIXMessageProcessor, IFIXSource, IHasAttributes, IMessageListener, IMessageProcessor, IMessageSource, IRegisterable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    LinkBase

    public interface ILink
extends IFIXListener, IFIXSource
    An ILink is a special message processor which is used to join together message processor chains.

    There are two sides to a link with one or more connection points (sessions) on one side and one or more connection points on the other side. The link joins the message processor chains for connection points on one side with the chains of the connection points on the other side.

    For example: 

        Session A              Session 1
    Session B     Link     Session 2
    Session C              Session 3

    Linking connection points in this way involves routing. Routing is done based on the party's associated with each message. For example, the connection points to route to may be determined from the Target and Sender parties (CompID's, SubID's and LocationID's) of a FIX message.

    Links can be directed or undirected. In a directed link, messages from the first group are routed to the second group (but not vice-versa). In an undirected links, messages from either group are routed to the other group.

      • getGroups

        IConnectionPoint[][] getGroups()
        The two groups of connection points corresponding to each side of the link.
        Returns:
        Two arrays of connection points - one for each side of the link.

      • isDirected

        boolean isDirected()
        True if this is a directed link.

        In that case link listens to connection points in first group and routes to connection points in second group. With non directed links, messages from either group are routed to the other group.

        Returns:
        True if directed link.

      • isUsingPartialConnectionPointMatching

        boolean isUsingPartialConnectionPointMatching()
        True if message processors listening to the link (on both sides) should accept messages using only partial connection point matching rather than the default complete connection point matching.
        Returns:
        True if partial connection point matching is configured, false otherwise.
        See Also:
        FIXMessageSelector

      • setGroups

        void setGroups(IConnectionPoint[][] groups)
        Set the connection points two-dimensional array in the link
        Parameters:
        groups - Two-dimensional array of connection points

      • isConcurrentRouting

        boolean isConcurrentRouting()
        If true, multiple sessions are allowed to route messages concurrently (i.e. in different threads), potentially to the same target session. This allows for more efficient processing but requires care with the implementation of message processors in the processing chain of the target sessions due to potential thread-safety issues. It false, only one session may route messages to another session at a time. This easier to implement, but it is possible for a sluggish target session to slow down the routing of other sessions.
        Returns:
        Whether the routing is concurrent or serial

      • isAnyToAny

        boolean isAnyToAny()
        True if this is any to any routing.

        In that case message from any session can be routed to any other session.

        Returns:
        True if any to any routing..
